FBIS3-21854 "jptdd011__l94066" JPRS-TDD-94-011-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 14 March 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA INDIA Agreement Signed With Burma To Check Drug Smuggling, Insurgency BK1003093194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 10 Mar 94 BK1003093194 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] India and Myanmar [Burma] have signed an agreement on checking drug smuggling and insurgency on the border. The six-point agreement was signed at the end of the three-day talks in Imphal yesterday by Mr. H.V. Goswamy, chief secretary of Manipur, and Mr. (Ohn Pyne), director-general Home Affairs, Myanmar. The talks were held as a follow-up of the memorandum of understanding signed by the Government of Myanmar and India in New Delhi in January for the maintenance of peace and tranquility along the border.
